				<outline text="I keep being introduced as being a Forbes 30 under 30 😅. No hate, but I've never been on any 30 under 30 list (I spent the majority of my 20s working temp jobs).Ty to everyone for assuming I'm much younger/more successful than I am!! I do not support any age based lists though&amp;lt;3" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 16:48:38 GMT" tweetId="1412453447530594310" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412453447530594310" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="No, I'm 50 and thriving &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/DanGarcia1980/status/1412453679240826885&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 16:51:09 GMT" tweetId="1412454080723800068" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412454080723800068" inReplyToId="1412453447530594310" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="“I’m scared that no matter what I do, I’ve become an enemy of the mob. No matter what I do, I’m just going to get hate” Good piece on what happened to @deannaschwartzz &amp;amp; what young journalists (especially women/POC) have to deal w/ in today's media climate &lt;a href=&quot;https://studyhall.xyz/newsletters/digest-07-06-2021/&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 16:33:20 GMT" tweetId="1412449596668788739" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412449596668788739" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;Everyone who uses social media inherently portrays a certain version of themselves while omitting the rest; playacting is the essence of the internet...Still, it’s become easier than ever to assume an almost entirely new identity online&quot; &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vox.com/the-goods/2021/7/6/22561197/coconutkitty-diana-deets-itsnotdatsrs-asianfishing-deepfake-catfish&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:35:32 GMT" tweetId="1412435052366008325" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412435052366008325" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="🔥🔥🔥 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/erinkwoo/status/1412431730326130691&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:26:38 GMT" tweetId="1412432811164844032" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412432811164844032" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="&quot;Asher is not part of a typical influencer collective. He is one of many members of a 29-person 'system,'  all of whom share a single body, brain, and life.&quot; Fascinating longread on Dissociative Identity Disorder TikTok by @stealthywriter_ in @inputmag &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.inputmag.com/culture/dissociative-identity-disorder-did-tiktok-influencers-multiple-personalities&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:23:04 GMT" tweetId="1412431912430342145" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412431912430342145" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="There are so many products that have gone viral on TikTok that people are opening stores dedicated to them. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vox.com/the-goods/22555723/tiktok-viral-products-cerave-sky-high-mascara-amazon-leggings&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 15:10:19 GMT" tweetId="1412428705616572417" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412428705616572417" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Iconic collab between 2 of my fave social media/creator economy experts @brendangahan @JayHoovy &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/brendangahan/status/1412424947889278976&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Tue, 06 Jul 2021 14:56:42 GMT" tweetId="1412425278060646412" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1412425278060646412" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
