				<outline text="Excited to chat with these fine folks about social media and internet stuff!! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/MorningBrew/status/1410669388873842690&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 18:50:57 GMT" tweetId="1410672287674560514" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410672287674560514" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="When will the creator economy reach the point where I get royalties for all the free content I’ve generated for meme accounts over the years? (this one from 2015 is still going!) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1410661424037208067/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 18:07:46 GMT" tweetId="1410661424037208067" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410661424037208067" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I’ve gone viral yet again on the Millennial meme pages 😅 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1410828234048954369/photo/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Fri, 02 Jul 2021 05:10:37 GMT" tweetId="1410828234048954369" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410828234048954369" inReplyToId="1410661424037208067" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="This man is an absolute master of his craft and I will watch every one of his videos &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/foundhergrail/status/1410602427556892672&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 17:53:26 GMT" tweetId="1410657814125502466" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410657814125502466" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="His videos are so perfect he deserves all the hype &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.tiktok.com/@theslappablejerk?_d=secCgYIASAHKAESMgowFLNDoZ%2Fu7xUFTmrG%2F5PUBqG6iRyazz1Yz0xaLOuop6DGenWUoV%2Fesosmh7z2vHhpGgA%3D&amp;checksum=3afbf9c4b273d8db2f37ab8d75e06296c77b22d73a6f3e6e5cbf183980fe19d3&amp;language=en&amp;sec_uid=MS4wLjABAAAAPsyVukojJ_W_Iaw6XhHRA2PSYF-QUpECBc_dyiPNqjlTY1gG6P8hkKTDmxkgMv4N&amp;sec_user_id=MS4wLjABAAAA4BgIbw0ed4-DdJrkIGl8b-Z7qVcLSeJC8LSb_o3Q8_UKKEk1hoyPyATFAQmpe-Go&amp;share_app_id=1233&amp;share_author_id=6919201259875517445&amp;share_link_id=A1CC560B-82FB-4110-958C-6F60CB3AC30E&amp;tt_from=copy&amp;u_code=6dc3cefl1fi8a&amp;user_id=144377784793104384&amp;utm_campaign=client_share&amp;utm_medium=ios&amp;utm_source=copy&amp;source=h5_m&amp;_r=1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt; https://t.co/KCJVV9CyGL" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 17:58:05 GMT" tweetId="1410658983979851781" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410658983979851781" inReplyToId="1410657814125502466" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="He nails it &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1410659126103867392/video/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 17:58:39 GMT" tweetId="1410659126103867392" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410659126103867392" inReplyToId="1410658983979851781" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="Never seen someone so good at being so toxic &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/TaylorLorenz/status/1410659700606070787/video/1&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 18:00:56 GMT" tweetId="1410659700606070787" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410659700606070787" inReplyToId="1410659126103867392" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="!!! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/gbaroth/status/1410651513978982401&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 17:34:33 GMT" tweetId="1410653064030158851" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410653064030158851" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="So excited for the @kieranpressreyn era on @thisisinsider &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/kieranpressreyn/status/1409980847713886214&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 16:42:41 GMT" tweetId="1410640010756321282" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410640010756321282" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text=".@kieranpressreyn wrote this piece recently for NYT that I was so jealous of &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.nytimes.com/2021/05/16/arts/music/roblox-video-game-music.html&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 16:43:49 GMT" tweetId="1410640296656863236" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410640296656863236" inReplyToId="1410640010756321282" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="So police are playing copyrighted music while being recorded in an attempt to ensure that the footage will get DMCAd when shared on social &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/APTPaction/status/1410633647670005760&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 16:28:29 GMT" tweetId="1410636435930062851" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410636435930062851" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Similar instance from back in February &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newsweek.com/california-police-officer-plays-music-copyright-social-media-livestream-1568253&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 16:29:23 GMT" tweetId="1410636662896402433" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410636662896402433" inReplyToId="1410636435930062851" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="&quot;In at least three cases, Beverly Hills Cops have started playing music seemingly to prevent themselves from being filmed by an activist.&quot; 

&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vice.com/en/article/bvxa7q/new-video-shows-beverly-hills-cops-playing-beatles-to-trigger-instagram-copyright-filter&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 16:31:25 GMT" tweetId="1410637176103047176" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410637176103047176" inReplyToId="1410636662896402433" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="Follow @dexdigi who has been covering this for a while &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.vice.com/en/article/wx89kn/it-sure-looks-like-this-cop-played-country-music-to-avoid-being-filmed&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 16:33:37 GMT" tweetId="1410637729788928002" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410637729788928002" inReplyToId="1410637176103047176" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The sexist/anti media people really don’t know what to do with a woman in her 30s. Am I a dumb “very young, much younger than most at the NYT” girl, like Tucker said? or am I an old hag who should retire b/c I’m still writing about culture in my mid 30s? They really can’t decide" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 15:28:58 GMT" tweetId="1410621458204684290" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410621458204684290" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="😌 &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ositanwanevu/status/1410609734231547914&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 15:01:04 GMT" tweetId="1410614435790548995" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410614435790548995" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="“The ad-peddling model that dominates the internet and hijacks our minds is costing us too much by being ‘free’” writes Substack CEO @cjgbest &lt;a href=&quot;https://blog.substack.com/p/breaking-off-the-engagement&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 14:55:27 GMT" tweetId="1410613025136996352" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410613025136996352" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				</outline>
			</outline>
		<outline text="June 2021" type="calendarMonth" name="june2021" >
			<outline text="June 30" type="calendarDay" name="30" >
				<outline text="It's so much more pervasive than people realize and is being fully weaponized used against journalists https://t.co/1mwAI7Zwbf" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 22:04:54 GMT" tweetId="1410358712330428416" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410358712330428416" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="The right wing media is so obsessed with me. This was a huge, public event that I was attending as press. 

There were managers, agents, industry execs, a red carpet, &amp;amp; parents of some ATL influencers I know really well. Also creator partnerships ppl from Dubsmash, Reddit, etc https://t.co/4DTlD3DY17" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 20:39:09 GMT" tweetId="1410337132103671814" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410337132103671814" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="These ppl are constantly try to smear me as some sort of child predator. It's full Qanon shit and people should call these campaigns out for what they are: gross attempts at silencing the press by smearing and attacking individual reporters, primarily women and POC" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 20:44:34 GMT" tweetId="1410338492568141826" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410338492568141826" inReplyToId="1410337132103671814" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="I don't talk about 99% of the stuff I've dealt with this past year publicly b/c it is legitimately terrifying. The brained poisoned people who read these sites truly believe me, Hillary Clinton, etc are abusing children, and it's scary what people will do when they believe that https://t.co/mmRfSRi34L" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 20:59:20 GMT" tweetId="1410342210361458689" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410342210361458689" inReplyToId="1410338492568141826" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="I've had to deal with a 24/7 barrage of these smears for a year and a half while performing at the *highest* level, under intense scrutiny and harassment, during a year of death and personal tragedy while the majority of people in this industry continue to not take this seriously" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 22:53:43 GMT" tweetId="1410370997958549509" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410370997958549509" inReplyToId="1410342210361458689" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
							<outline text="It’s so telling what outlets constantly cover these “stories” about me. 

This one is labeled “Patriots Push Back” and “Patriots only!” https://t.co/08vPhhYAcx" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 00:00:33 GMT" tweetId="1410387813376266243" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410387813376266243" inReplyToId="1410342210361458689" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="“We’re no longer a photo-sharing app or a square photo-sharing app,” said @mosseri https://t.co/HA1iCxQ6o7" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 19:58:09 GMT" tweetId="1410326812253556736" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410326812253556736" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="A six-month Times investigation has synchronized and mapped out thousands of videos and police radio communications from the Jan. 6 Capitol riot, providing the most complete picture to date of what happened — and why https://t.co/paPs5W9vEJ" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 19:41:46 GMT" tweetId="1410322689571450883" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410322689571450883" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Venmo pulling the Jeffree Star PR playbook https://t.co/0mroeZhQe9" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 19:40:49 GMT" tweetId="1410322450332536833" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410322450332536833" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="IG is finally productizing what influencers have been doing for years now (charging people to subscribe to their Close Friends content) https://t.co/W8rhalvCZ8" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 15:50:13 GMT" tweetId="1410264417665642499" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410264417665642499" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="You should be able to post to mutuals only or close friends on twitter" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 14:36:02 GMT" tweetId="1410245747778326532" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410245747778326532" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Psyched to see Twitter exploring this!! &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/a_dsgnr/status/1410690425963180032&quot;&gt;[link]&lt;/a&gt;" type="tweet" created="Thu, 01 Jul 2021 20:29:02 GMT" tweetId="1410696973842223107" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410696973842223107" inReplyToId="1410245747778326532" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="This is literally not true and I had absolutely zero to do with Choire leaving NYT. Please stop trying to relate every story about the NYT back to me https://t.co/NzsaXrsE57" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 06:37:35 GMT" tweetId="1410125341901791233" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410125341901791233" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="In zero way do I “engage with online critics” other than by speaking broadly about .001% of the harassment and BS I’ve had to deal with online. Stop acting like this is a 2 sided thing, it’s not. Media organizations should not treat it that way." type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 06:39:40 GMT" tweetId="1410125867288719360" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410125867288719360" inReplyToId="1410125341901791233" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="These ppl aren’t “critics”, their goal is to smear and attack reporters they consider vulnerable. They make entire news cycles abt me saying I’m tired or celebrating international women’s day. This is not good faith “criticism”. Not that I’d expect Daily Beast to know the diff" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 06:44:44 GMT" tweetId="1410127143149850629" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410127143149850629" inReplyToId="1410125867288719360" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					<outline text="In zero way do I “engage with online critics” other than by speaking broadly about .001% of the harassment and BS I’ve had to deal with online. Stop acting like this is a 2 sided thing, it’s not. Media organizations should not treat it that way." type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 06:39:40 GMT" tweetId="1410125867288719360" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410125867288719360" inReplyToId="1410125341901791233" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="June 29" type="calendarDay" name="29" >
				<outline text="@Sodapoppintv check DM 🙏🏻" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 01:00:08 GMT" tweetId="1410040419753234434" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410040419753234434" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Just contemplating what this could mean for C*risti*n’s TikTok career https://t.co/zE8V4THhi4" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 00:47:12 GMT" tweetId="1410037168689487876" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1410037168689487876" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="No offense please here, but seeing a few takes like this online and *this* is the “worst kind of tech “criticism”. It’s just as important to cover labor issues and exploitation when women are the bosses as when men are. https://t.co/OBf97i7yV4" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 21:30:32 GMT" tweetId="1409987676271366151" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409987676271366151" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="I do agree with Paul on this, there are a million male Holmes. The solution isn’t to allow women to exploit more people, it’s to hold the men doing the same things as accountable. https://t.co/Qzh4xR33kf" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 21:32:09 GMT" tweetId="1409988080849674246" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409988080849674246" inReplyToId="1409987676271366151" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="“Female founder implosion stories” also cover companies that matter to lots of women. Those stories are important to tell! We should not be doing less of that, the media should just hold men to the same standards (as many women tech reporters have been trying to do for years)" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 21:35:01 GMT" tweetId="1409988802773340163" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409988802773340163" inReplyToId="1409988080849674246" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="What the actual fuck is the matter with this account. This is sick. This young woman wrote a brilliant and personal piece on something SO many young people have struggled with and all these ppl are now mocking and harassing her. It’s disgusting https://t.co/HQDA91yTpQ" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 20:15:02 GMT" tweetId="1409968673104621572" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409968673104621572" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text=".@deannaschwartzz is one of the most brilliant, empathetic, dogged young reporters. She wrote about young ppl being robbed of pivotal experiences during Covid. And these fucked up people online want to mock her for not having her first kiss. https://t.co/8NaR6nCSTb" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 20:20:17 GMT" tweetId="1409969993635090432" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409969993635090432" inReplyToId="1409968673104621572" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="I am so angry about what @deannaschwartzz is being put through. Is this the “welcome to media” experience we want talented young women in the industry to have to endure? It’s fucked up beyond belief. Please send love and encouragement to @deannaschwartzz https://t.co/xoKLYaaJmF" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 20:25:21 GMT" tweetId="1409971269429125120" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409971269429125120" inReplyToId="1409969993635090432" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="All these platforms need Waymo editors https://t.co/63znzoOTpL" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 18:53:34 GMT" tweetId="1409948171392880641" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409948171392880641" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Real Life is the one website where I think I can confidently say I’ve read everything on it. Just subbed to their newsletter too https://t.co/2OXnRIJuIb" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 17:44:20 GMT" tweetId="1409930750577700867" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409930750577700867" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I think about this meme @rebexxxxa made on a daily basis https://t.co/KWOGhLVB06" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:40:00 GMT" tweetId="1409914558685220865" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409914558685220865" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="A few young writers have messaged me lately about worrying their pieces aren’t definitive enough, or they worry other ppl are judging them for their work, and I just want them and everyone to know (to put it in the context of the meme), we have all done the Cheetos interview" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:49:28 GMT" tweetId="1409916939934134286" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409916939934134286" inReplyToId="1409914558685220865" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="I’m so grateful for the attention my stories get &amp;amp; the work I do now, but I’ve been slogging through the digital media food chain for 12 years. Sometimes it takes a while, and you have to write mortifying sponcon for a year that your byline is forever attached to 🥴 https://t.co/jFIikIPlS0" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:55:07 GMT" tweetId="1409918364613419008" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409918364613419008" inReplyToId="1409916939934134286" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="If ur worried your work isn’t perfect or you have to write up a bunch of dumb SEO hits for your job, don’t stress or let it define you. It’s the reality of digital media unfortunately, and just know most all of us (millennial journalists at least) have been there. No judgement💓" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:59:39 GMT" tweetId="1409919502825922566" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409919502825922566" inReplyToId="1409918364613419008" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="Once I interviewed for a tech reporter job right after I published a story on a man using his own shit to paint a portrait of Mark Zuckerberg. I was so embarrassed bc I wanted to be a “serious” writer. But that whole construct is dumb and those jobs haven’t existed since the 90s https://t.co/J28iUFOo2C" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 17:07:08 GMT" tweetId="1409921387444137990" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409921387444137990" inReplyToId="1409919502825922566" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
								</outline>
							</outline>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Only thing I'd add to this is the role &quot;snark&quot;/gossip communities play in all this, pushing these narratives &amp;amp; tearing ppl down. So much &quot;drama&quot; that gets picked up by media is just hate campaigns bubbling up from GOMI-like communities pushing a narrative https://t.co/7pBoCruEMC" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:01:25 GMT" tweetId="1409904849773228032" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409904849773228032" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="This all ties back into a certain strain of &quot;accountability&quot; culture, which @cwarzel wrote a great piece on recently too  https://t.co/pbLwM0SEkE" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:03:08 GMT" tweetId="1409905281178296323" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409905281178296323" inReplyToId="1409904849773228032" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="Definitley read this whole piece by @rebexxxxa on influencer drama, such a smart comparison to horse race journalism. https://t.co/7pBoCruEMC https://t.co/1qWVcoRklU" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 16:08:04 GMT" tweetId="1409906524084858883" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409906524084858883" inReplyToId="1409905281178296323" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="NELK's monetization strategy (shunning ad revenue and productizing themselves) is a strategy that's increasingly pursued by creators, and gives YouTube even less of an ability to play kingmaker and police the platform https://t.co/ezxqsb7Ofe" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:54:55 GMT" tweetId="1409903215471071243" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409903215471071243" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="Demonetizing channels (youtube's primary form of punishment) doesn't carry much weight when creators are making tens of thousands of $$ from more direct revenue streams https://t.co/ezxqsb7Ofe" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:57:19 GMT" tweetId="1409903817953402887" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409903817953402887" inReplyToId="1409903215471071243" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="They're multiplying https://t.co/4fs2CXOTEA" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:52:10 GMT" tweetId="1409902520969826305" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409902520969826305" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text=".@kathrynfiona wrote about the Glitch Queen https://t.co/LYsJCJMKkc" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:45:00 GMT" tweetId="1409900716957782017" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409900716957782017" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Oh great https://t.co/up9M5l8oLv https://t.co/4RfD3RL0il" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:13:00 GMT" tweetId="1409892663885770752" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409892663885770752" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Given FB's history of incentivizing certain people and content on the platform for years, I'm eager to see how well this line ages https://t.co/nSPVS7YP1u https://t.co/b417DS8mGn" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 15:05:00 GMT" tweetId="1409890651173494784" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409890651173494784" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I wrote about NELK, some of the top earning creators on YouTube, who take zero money from YouTube  https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:10:58 GMT" tweetId="1409877053466349569" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409877053466349569" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="The NELK boys are set to make over $70M from merch alone this year, their Happy Dad seltzer line is causing mobs outside liquor stores across California, they have a wildly popular proprietary subscription platform, and more. https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:19:00 GMT" tweetId="1409879075825586186" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409879075825586186" inReplyToId="1409877053466349569" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="We’re not going to sacrifice our content or change to make $500,000 a month from YouTube. Maybe in the short term we’re not buying Lambos like other YouTubers, but we could have a multibillion-dollar business on our hands.” https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:19:56 GMT" tweetId="1409879309221871620" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409879309221871620" inReplyToId="1409879075825586186" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="“With our audience, we can build pretty much anything. Maybe we start a men’s grooming company or we could sell condoms if we wanted to. We could open Full Send gyms. We could do pizza delivery.” https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:21:59 GMT" tweetId="1409879826106880014" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409879826106880014" inReplyToId="1409879309221871620" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="Shahidi imagines Nelk someday competing with multinational corporations like Amazon, Anheuser Bush, Apple, and Uber. &quot;Nelk could have an entire network of drivers that can eventually deliver anything that’s in our ecosystem.&quot; https://t.co/ezxqsbppDO" type="tweet" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 14:23:39 GMT" tweetId="1409880246929743877" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409880246929743877" inReplyToId="1409879826106880014" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
								</outline>
