				<outline text=".@kathrynfiona on the digital-media-to-Netflix pipeline and more https://t.co/Ut5UpG4iBG" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:28:57 GMT" tweetId="1409594688588365824" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409594688588365824" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Only in the past year has the tech industry as a whole started to recognize influencers as businesses (and many still have sexist notions &quot;influencer&quot; is vs &quot;creator,&quot; which are the same thing). I think as the space continues to grow in terms of $ more ppl will recognize it! https://t.co/iEoocBC5ng" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:21:32 GMT" tweetId="1409592821804244997" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409592821804244997" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="There are actually several LLCs called Instagram Husband or some version of that I'm sorry to report 😅 https://t.co/hQLdCJgvro https://t.co/cdWOclw5RZ" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:10:53 GMT" tweetId="1409590142864486401" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409590142864486401" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="FaZe Clan, Jeffree Star, MrBeast, Arielle Charnas and MANY more influencers received PPP loans. I know people don't like to think of it this way but creator-led companies are the fastest growing type of small business! https://t.co/ZGmePOwsnm" type="tweet" created="Mon, 28 Jun 2021 19:14:09 GMT" tweetId="1409590964570656768" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1409590964570656768" inReplyToId="1409590142864486401" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
