				<outline text="Brooklyn is back 😌 https://t.co/0ZurGILUFt" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 21:22:40 GMT" tweetId="1408536143834931200" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408536143834931200" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Looks like that YouTubers vs TikTokers event didn’t do so well, the company behind it put out a statement in response to many creators who allege they still haven’t been paid. 
 
Company says it’s their “sincere hope” to be able to pay all the talent in a “reasonable timeframe” https://t.co/R8KM6zzhWg" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 21:15:15 GMT" tweetId="1408534275691991040" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408534275691991040" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="SCOOP: William White, who has gained a massive audience of older women by playing an 80s heartthrob on TikTok, has signed with WME https://t.co/xiyb5OfQFb" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 21:01:54 GMT" tweetId="1408530916092219393" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408530916092219393" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="William White has signed with IMG Modeling and WME talent agency, his manager will continue to manage him https://t.co/xiyb5OfQFb" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 21:05:47 GMT" tweetId="1408531892417097728" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408531892417097728" inReplyToId="1408530916092219393" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
					</outline>
				<outline text="Thread https://t.co/sA5bRow00s" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:09:10 GMT" tweetId="1408457247080927240" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408457247080927240" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Got to collab with the brilliant @laurnosa on this story on TikTok, Black creators, and how the rise of the &quot;creator economy&quot; is reshaping people's views of creative labor https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 16:05:17 GMT" tweetId="1408456272806957065" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408456272806957065" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Instead trying to be hot I propose a slob girl summer https://t.co/poxrx7fq6l" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:40:27 GMT" tweetId="1408450020454531072" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408450020454531072" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="Yeah that's one thing to note too, SO many dance trends on TikTok start internationally https://t.co/2QYDhK01JT" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:38:46 GMT" tweetId="1408449597165375489" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408449597165375489" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
				<outline text="I wrote about the Black TikTok creator &quot;strike&quot; and shifting norms around labor and the creator economy https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:08:11 GMT" tweetId="1408441901489950722" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408441901489950722" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
					<outline text="To frame this as an issue around dance credits misses the point. It's about so much more &amp;amp; speaks to broader issues of labor in the creator econ. “We are being exploited, and that’s the core issue Black folks have always had in terms of labor,” Erick said https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:12:39 GMT" tweetId="1408443024745533455" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408443024745533455" inReplyToId="1408441901489950722" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
						<outline text="“These millions of likes, that should all translate to something. How do we get real money, power and proper compensation we deserve?” https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:13:07 GMT" tweetId="1408443141695234055" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408443141695234055" inReplyToId="1408443024745533455" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
							<outline text="“The strike to send a message. The business models of these apps, they have us out here overworking and being underpaid. We’re working long hours but at the end of the day we’re still making little to nothing, and we Black creators are making even less.” https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:13:47 GMT" tweetId="1408443311694565376" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408443311694565376" inReplyToId="1408443141695234055" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
								<outline text="“My hope is that we realize this is an entire class of work that didn’t previously exist,” said @ljin18. “If we don’t offer this class of workers protections and rights, they’re going to become increasingly disenfranchised.” https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:15:19 GMT" tweetId="1408443697746702337" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408443697746702337" inReplyToId="1408443311694565376" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
									<outline text="@ljin18 Creators, especially Black creators, are finally recognizing the value they generate for these multi billion dollar tech companies and are asking for more https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa https://t.co/Pra8Gc489R" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:17:35 GMT" tweetId="1408444266481786883" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408444266481786883" inReplyToId="1408443697746702337" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
										<outline text="@ljin18 Kaelyn Kastle, a Black creator in Atlanta put it this way, &quot;We're working so hard to sustain these apps while trying to build something for ourselves and getting little to nothing out of it. These apps expect us to be happy with just building an audience.&quot; https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:18:48 GMT" tweetId="1408444573102133251" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408444573102133251" inReplyToId="1408444266481786883" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
											<outline text="Even before the &quot;strike,&quot; dance trends on TikTok have been declining &amp;amp; the trends associated with many top audios have not included dances. Despite tweets suggesting otherwise, the trend most popularly associated w/ Thot Shit was never dance related. https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:22:46 GMT" tweetId="1408445572181204992" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408445572181204992" inReplyToId="1408444573102133251" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
												<outline text="TikToks top creators have transitioned away from dancing toward more vlogging and YouTube-style content. As the pandemic wanes, average users are also spending more time outside their homes creating a more diverse range of content as the app evolves https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:24:12 GMT" tweetId="1408445931045806083" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408445931045806083" inReplyToId="1408445572181204992" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" >
													<outline text="“The shift away from dance takes even more of the megaphone away from these Black creators,” said Kwasi Ohene-Adu, the founder of Groovetime, a platform for creators to own and monetize their dances. https://t.co/lp5DN0xpKa" type="tweet" created="Fri, 25 Jun 2021 15:30:59 GMT" tweetId="1408447640962961408" urltweet="https://twitter.com/taylorlorenz/status/1408447640962961408" inReplyToId="1408445931045806083" tweetUserName="taylorlorenz" />
													</outline>
												</outline>
